<p>To eliminate the extended attributes of <strong>Textmate</strong> execute the following command on Terminal:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>defaults write com.macromates.textmate OakDocumentDisableFSMetaData 1  
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>This will eliminate the <strong>@</strong> of the permissions of the files, those which we can see executing <code class="highlighter-rouge">ls -al</code> (-rw-râ€“râ€“@)
Also this will allow to copy this files to systems that doesnâ€™t suppport extended attributes (like Samba), and not see files <strong><em>._filename</em></strong> created at all.</p>
